    "question_id" : 3434363,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you're using eclipse with PHP package and want to change highlighted colour then there is slight difference to above answer.</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Right click on highlighted word</li>\n<li>Select 'Preferences'</li>\n<li>Go to General > Editors > Text Editors > Annotations. Now look for \"PHP elements 'read' occurrences\" and \"PHP elements 'write' occurrences\". You can select your desired colour there.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/zUJVO.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/zUJVO.png\" alt=\"Change Highlighted text colour in Eclips with PHP\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
